        <div id="paragraphs">
          <div id="location">
            <div>Location of Greece</div>
            Greece is located in the south east of Europe in the Balkans, it
            consists of thousands of little islands all throughout the seas
            surrounding it. Greece was very important in ancient times and thus
            has some historic and famous landmarks such as the Acropolis,
            located in the capital of Greece, Athens. Within the Acropolis,
            there is the most famous landmark of all of Greece, the Parthenon.
            This is a temple built to honour the goddess Athena, who represents
            wisdom and craft and has stood intact for thousands of years amongst
            wars and battles and time. She is also said to be watching over
            Athens to this day. Also located in Athens is the Temple of the
            Olympian Zeus, which in ancient times was built to honour the god
            Zeus who was seen as the ruler of the gods on Mount Olympus.
          </div>

          <div id="regions">
            <div>Important Cities</div>
            The most important city in Greece is Athens. Since ancient times,
            this city has been the largest, most populated, and most advanced
            city in Greece, and in ancient times, one of the most influential in
            the world. While it has always been large and populated, Athens was
            home to some of the best philosophers in history, some of the best
            inventors, and also the birthplace of democracy. A political system
            still used across the world to this day with very little changes.
            The architecture was also ahead of its time due to the amount of
            amazingly talented architects living in Athens. <br />
            The second most important city in Greece is Thessaloniki. This is
            because it has the second highest population, as well as in ancient
            Greece, it was the hub of supplys to and from Greece. All shipments
            being sent to other countries, or coming into Greece were sent into
            Thessaloniki.
          </div>
        </div>

